postcontent: This pistol is 1 of 10,000 1911A1s made by COLT for the Argentine Army.  This unique group of pistols are collectively know as "THE 1927 HARTFORD ARGENTINE ARMY MODELS".These 10,000 Hartford Colts were ordered by the Argentine Governement for their military in 1927.  They were delivered from 1928 to 1933 and marked using consequitive serial numbers 1 thru 10,000.  This pistol up for sale is #1270.  Serial numbers were stamped in Colt's italic font on top of the slides, under the mainspring housing, and on the top of the barrel.On the left side of the slide is stamped "COLT'S PT. F.A. MFG. CO. HARTFORD CT. USA  PATD APR. 20, 1897,SEPT. 9, 1902,DEC. 19, 1905,FEB. 14, 1911,AUG. 19, 1913."On the right side of the slide is stamped the Argentine Crest and: "EJERCITO ARGENTINO  COLT CAL. 45 MOD. 1927".These Colts are rare in that only 10,000 were ever made.  They are also rare in another manner as they were some of the first transition models which implemented design changes from the old 1911 Model to the new 1911A1 Model.  Price is $1300 or Best Offer
